The paper focuses on improving the generalizability of convolutional neural network (CNN)-based face antispoofing methods across different kinds of datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a deep domain transfer CNN using sparsely unlabeled data, which indicates that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper deals with face spoofing attacks, which may fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. As the paper discusses the limitations of current approaches to face antispoofing, it may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for improving the generalizability of face antispoofing, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
